{
  "text": "Examples of classical macrosociological research Rozov cites are not very convincing. Contrary to the opinion of Durkheim and according to current studies, around 75-90% of suicides are connected to various mental illnesses or psychiatric deviations (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Conwell et al. 1996) . This fact, though, does not contradict the Durkheim's conclusion about the relationship between individualism and frequency of suicide because of the rarity of suicides in the general population. However, in Russia and other countries the majority of suicides are related not to individualism or collectivism but to immoderate alcohol consumption or to its social consequences (Alcohol Catastrophe 2008; Cher 2006) .",
  "citation_candidates": [
